  "text": "To further examine the eIF2B␣ homodimers observed in the MS data, we first examined its crystal structure [CITATION_1] . It showed homodimerization of eIF2B␣ via the Rossmann fold-like domains toward the C terminus of the subunit (Fig. 2A) . This arrangement has also been observed in several sequence and structural homologues, including the archaeal homologue aIF2B␣ (pdb:1T9K) and ribose 5-phosphate isomerase (pdb: 2YRF), both of which possess a similar monomeric structure containing a helical bundle and Rossmann fold. Both homodimerize via the Rossmann fold domain in a manner similar to that observed in the eIF2B␣ structure.",
